The General Officer Commanding (GOC) 1 Mechanised Division of the Nigerian Army headquarters Kaduna, Maj. Gen. Faruk Yahaya, has laid the foundation of the project of Retired Army, Navy, Air force Officers (RANAO) Association Kaduna State chapter. The project which is worth N14,000,000 is part of the effort of the present leadership of the association under the chairmanship of Col. Daniel Idoko (retired). Represented by the training Officer, Brigadier General Valentine Okoro, the GOC  said that 1 Division Nigerian Army is glad with what present leadership of RANAO is doing especially the legacy they want to leave behind. He therefore urged them to sustain the good works while assuring them of the support of the 1 mechanised division under his leadership to see to the completion of the project. Major Yahaya further reiterated that the Nigerian Army is ever ready to give listening ears to RANAO whenever the need arises. Earlier in his address, the chairman of the association, Kaduna State chapter, Colonel Idoko (retired) challenged the Chapter, and patrons as well as other well-wishers to come to the aid of the chapter, particularly with the ongoing viable project. According to him, “What we are witnessing today is our gallant response to the ‘noble’ advice and challenge by GOC. We have taxed ourselves by contributing 1% of our Pension Arrears that was paid early this year”. Also speaking,  the president of the association, Major General Alexander Mshelbwala (retired) commended the Kaduna State chapter of the association noting that the objectives of the association is to ensure the  comfort and welfare of its members, adding that such project will enhance wellbeing of  their members. Mshelbwala extended his appreciation to the Kaduna chairman of the association for his tireless efforts while urging members to ensure that they give him the required support to complete the project.